At least 21 people have been killed in a bus crash in the Eastern Cape. The bus was travelling from Chebe to Butterworth. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - At least 21 people have been killed in a bus crash in the Eastern Cape. The bus was travelling from Centane to Butterworth when it plunged down an embankment. READ:Â Six injured in Durban crash Simon Zwane, the spokesperson for the Road Traffic Management Corporation, says the driver lost control of the bus resulting in the fatal crash. The RTMC has described the crash as the worst bus accident in the last five years. 